answer.text: "The Blood Orange Wheat beer is usually really good and one of my favorite beers. However,  the last couple of time I have been in there is has tasted bitter and not as thick and rich as usual. I would recommend buying it in the can, which is consistently good.  As other reviews have noted,  the service is meh at best. The bartenders are often standoffish and seem to have an attitude.  Most brew pubs have friendly and knowledgeable staff. This place seems to attract mostly the opposite.   With just a slightly friendlier staff, a TV that faces the bar or even a person playing guitar in the corner this place would be great. For now I'll just get the canned beer and drink it in the company of friendly people at my house."

answer.text: "The key card was brown and seemed like it had never been cleaned.
